No matter what anyone says about my local library.. our library staff very friendly,  calm, they are pillars in our society who encourage our kids to read , co ducting reading challenges summer,  they make little book markers with summary of books. They always..have themed writer/books in the centre displayed in children section encouraging children to read them. You need to visit library more often.. know people who works there..before criticising them.

This Library has really good collection for children. Staff are very friendly, cheerful and helpful. The staff are always there to guide you to find relevant books for school projects,  dyslexic friendly,  classic to modern, fiction and non fiction . The library has quite and calm environment for adults and children. We are lucky to have this building and dedicated staff.

Functional relic of a bygone era. Holding out for the restoration of the former Borough of Hornsey which it still proudly displays on its facade. Feels like any civic managed library back in the 1980s rather than the shiny multi purpose learning and community space that other libraries have become.

I don't live locally and had occasion to visit (by appointment) the library archives section. I found I was expected and all the stuff I needed was set out immaculately for me. I and my accompanying grandson were treated very well and made welcome. A good experience and the individual who took care of us was: Clare Stephens, who I can recommend as a fine professional. So, well done one and all.

address: Queens Ave, Muswell Hill, London N10 3PE, United Kingdom
